    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "“Preserve me, O God, for in Thee I confide”—"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "In God He took refuge whate’er did betide."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "“O Thou art my Lord, I’ve no good beyond Thee”—"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "He spoke in Himself unto God constantly."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "2"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "“As for all the saints who are dwelling on earth,”"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "To Him they’re the people of excellent worth."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Of them He has said He has all His delight—"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "In proving this all the four Gospels unite."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "3"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "“The Lord is my portion, the Lord is my cup”—"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "For everything He to the Father looked up."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "“The Lord I will bless who my counsel doth give”—"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Himself He denied and by God’s word did live."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "4"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "His heart thus was glad and His spirit rejoiced,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And e’en in His death praise to God could be voiced;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "His soul God would never abandon to hell,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "But in resurrection His body would dwell."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "5"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "God raised Him, and He with God’s glory was crowned;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Then fulness of joy in God’s presence He found."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "E’en now at the Father’s right hand is His seat,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Where flowing forever are pleasures complete."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "6"
    }
